                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/1351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Vice Consul in Charge of the Legation in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Longyear</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-30T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. For General Russell.</p>
                <p>Your August 26, noon.</p>
                <p>You will inform the Haitian Government that this Government is gratified to
                    receive the assurance conveyed in note referred to and that it desires to
                    suggest the advisability of forwarding a copy of the draft of the law
                    authorizing the issue of bonds of Series “B” to the Department before its
                    presentation to the Council of State. This will make it possible for the
                    Financial Adviser to study the matter and to make any suggestions which may
                    appear advisable. There would appear to be ample time to forward telegraphic
                    summary of the project before consideration by Council of State.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
